metaData.descriptionCS:
The child is presented with two or three rows of pictures and chooses one picture from each row to form a group
with a common characteristic.

questions.title: Sample Item A
questions.correctInstructionsHTML:
Correct response:

Say, That’s right. This tree (point to response option 2) goes with this tree (point to response option 3). They are both trees. Let’s try another one.
questions.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Say, That’s not quite right. This tree (point to response option 2) goes with this tree (point to response option 3). They are both trees. Let’s try another one.
questions.topInstructionsHTML: Say, Look up here (point across first row). Look down here (point across second row). Pick one here (point across first row) that goes with one here (point across second row).

questions.title: Sample Item B
questions.correctInstructionsHTML:
Correct response:

Say, That’s right. This squirrel (point to response option 1) goes with this bird (point to response option 3). They are both animals. Let’s try some more.
questions.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Say, That’s not quite right. This squirrel (point to response option 1) goes with this bird (point to response option 3). They are both animals. Let’s try some more.
questions.topInstructionsHTML: Say, Pick one here (point across first row) that goes with one here (point across second row).
